Paul:
What are you doing here, Libby?

51:04.349 --> 51:07.517
Libby: It was my day
on the meal rotation,

51:07.552 --> 51:11.888
and I thought you might like
some braised chicken.

51:14.776 --> 51:18.278
But maybe I shouldn't be
so presumptuous,

51:18.313 --> 51:22.448
reading your mind
about what you... might want.

51:24.736 --> 51:27.153
Paul:
Well, what do you want?

51:31.576 --> 51:33.243
Libby: You.

51:37.716 --> 51:38.965
Paul: [ Sighs ]

51:39.000 --> 51:41.334
Libby: You were right.

51:41.386 --> 51:45.838
I am-- I am so sick
of pretending all the time.

51:45.840 --> 51:46.839
[ Sighs ]

51:50.512 --> 51:52.895
This is where I want to be.

51:52.931 --> 51:55.898
♪

52:09.664 --> 52:12.799
Nora:
I don't tell people that--

52:12.834 --> 52:16.202
what a mess everything was
when I was growing up.

52:16.237 --> 52:18.454
William: Well, a sad childhood

52:18.506 --> 52:21.507
is not something people
often discuss.

52:21.543 --> 52:25.378
Nora: I won't even tell
my boyfriends.

52:25.430 --> 52:26.713
Although some of mine,

52:26.715 --> 52:29.282
they actually ended up
being like my father.

52:31.186 --> 52:32.468
William: That's a--
[ Clears throat ]

52:32.520 --> 52:33.720
A common phenomenon.

52:33.722 --> 52:34.887
[ Chuckles ]

52:36.808 --> 52:37.890
Nora: I even felt it a bit

52:37.892 --> 52:39.192
when you were angry with me
just then.

52:41.396 --> 52:42.562
William: Felt it?

52:45.200 --> 52:47.317
Nora: It made me...

52:47.369 --> 52:48.835
drawn to you.

52:51.456 --> 52:52.572
William: Well, you know,

52:52.574 --> 52:55.124
it's good that you can
catch yourself now

52:55.160 --> 52:57.377
when you see those patterns
repeating.

52:58.546 --> 53:00.663
Nora: And it's good I have
someone I can talk to about it.

53:02.751 --> 53:04.917
William:
Yes. That's good, too.

53:10.291 --> 53:12.458
Virginia:
I've always been the one

53:12.494 --> 53:15.595
that slips out the back door
before the party's over

53:15.630 --> 53:18.231
without saying...

53:18.266 --> 53:19.666
[ Sighs ]

53:19.701 --> 53:21.768
much of anything, really.

53:23.138 --> 53:26.139
Dan: Bad at endings, huh?

53:26.174 --> 53:28.207
I've been accused of that,
myself.

53:30.845 --> 53:32.011
Virginia: So...

53:38.620 --> 53:44.490
I don't go to New York
very often, but...

53:44.526 --> 53:46.859
if I do,
I will certainly--

53:46.895 --> 53:48.394
Dan: You'll look me up.

53:53.201 --> 53:54.300
Virginia: I will.

54:03.561 --> 54:05.578
Dan: You don't have to worry
about New York.

54:10.585 --> 54:13.720
Virginia: All right.

54:13.755 --> 54:15.221
I understand.

54:19.244 --> 54:21.794
Dan: Because I'll still
be coming to St. Louis.

54:23.631 --> 54:25.965
Virginia: But...

54:26.000 --> 54:27.083
you said yourself

54:27.135 --> 54:29.635
that we have come
to the end of the road.

54:29.671 --> 54:32.054
Dan: I don't care
about the road.

54:32.140 --> 54:33.723
What if I just came for you?

54:33.758 --> 54:36.592
Virginia: No.

54:36.644 --> 54:38.144
I mean...

54:39.597 --> 54:40.847
it doesn't work like that.

54:40.849 --> 54:42.014
Dan: Well, it may not.

54:44.269 --> 54:46.152
But the thought
of not seeing you every day

54:46.187 --> 54:48.187
is not something
I'm ready to accept just now.

54:52.694 --> 54:55.962
So, what if
I keep coming here...

54:56.030 --> 54:59.165
because we love each other?

54:59.200 --> 55:02.168
♪

